{"type":"message","id":"05f61caf","parentId":"2046a10d","timestamp":"2026-04-15T13:50:31.593Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_8f4fqu2shvyq_2","toolName":"memory_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"e9d45b8084ec25c26a57011ff7867aeb2686680293466a3f0c40a37ac384e957\",\n      \"path\": \"memory/2026-04-15.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 76,\n      \"endLine\": 114,\n      \"score\": 0.7872133268626856,\n      \"textScore\": 0.7872133268626856,\n      \"snippet\": \"- **Per day** → 1,440 new entries\\n- **sessions.json grows ~0.5-1MB/day**\\n\\n**Recommended fix**: Disable or throttle heartbeat cron, or implement session entry cleanup in the cron config.\\n\\n### Known Baseline (Not Issues)\\n- AHV Works review sessions from Apr 12-14: completed successfully (security.md, frontend.md written)\\n- DTLX subagent failures: pre-existing, `providerSpecificData` API errors (known)\\n- DTLX JWT `doc.id → doc._id` bug: still pending fix in token.service.js\\n\\n\\n## 09:56 UTC — Structural Fix: Heartbeat Throttled\\n\\n### Decision: Throttle heartbeat crons 5min → 15min\\n\\n**Why not disable?** Need monitoring for active sessions + agent failures. On-demand-only loses change detection.\\n\\n**\\n\\nSource: memory/2026-04-15.md#L76-L114\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"citation\": \"memory/2026-04-15.md#L76-L114\",\n      \"corpus\": \"memory\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"3ce84fdccb34bb4411c29ee2fce1e2b77b809351a57dc0fbfeb62334e2cc9446\",\n      \"path\": \"memory/2026-04-15.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 55,\n      \"endLine\": 82,\n      \"score\": 0.681357150047055,\n      \"textScore\": 0.681357150047055,\n      \"snippet\": \"- Root cause: Heartbeat cron creates 1 new session entry/minute\\n- Sessions marked \\\"running\\\" but actually aborted/stale — never cleaned\\n- cron:e7885813 (Agent Status to Lead) stuck in `sessions_send` retry loop\\n\\n### Actions Taken\\n1. **sessions.json**: Reduced from 5.7MB → 0.5MB (91% reduction)\\n   - 581 stale entries purged (>2h old or dead status)\\n   - 41 active entries retained\\n   - Backup: `sessions.json.bak`\\n2. **cron/runs/**: 19 stale cron run files removed (>3h old)\\n   - Retained: `e7885813` (2.5h), `ed2d0b5d` (active), `6f3323ef` (active)\\n3. **cron:e7885813** (Agent Status) killed — stuck retrying `sessions_send` to Lead direct session\\n\\n### Current Active Sessions (Live)\\n- `ed2d0b5d` (Q\\n\\nSource: memory/2026-04-15.md#L55-L82\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"citation\": \"memory/2026-04-15.md#L55-L82\",\n      \"corpus\": \"memory\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"74e72ca5a6ddc1253e28b2a02a7319ee3ab0d0f84500849aa8b9b30e4cffbd67\",\n      \"path\": \"memory/2026-04-15.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 26,\n      \"endLine\": 61,\n      \"score\": 0.6811620524137876,\n      \"textScore\": 0.6811620524137876,\n      \"snippet\": \"- Telegram group delivery via sessions_send: TIMEOUT (session not responding)\\n- Report composed but not delivered — Telegram infrastructure issue\\n\\n## 06:16 UTC — Daily Briefing\\n- QLHV BE MR !6 pending Lead review\\n- AHV Works: 13 P0 issues pending\\n- DTLX BE running on port 5555 ✅\\n- DTLX FE running on port 3000 ✅\\n- Pipeline HEALTHY at briefing time ✅\\n- cron:e7885813 already DEGRADED at briefing time\\n\\n## Notes\\n- `heartbeat-state.json` was empty/disabled — no baseline available for comparison\\n- Telegram delivery to group -5163901258 is unreliable (timeouts)\\n- Agent Status cron delivery issue is persistent across many cycles\\n\\n## 09:34 UTC — 5p Heartbeat\\n- QLHV Group session ended normally (~09:30\\n\\nSource: memory/2026-04-15.md#L26-L61\",\n      \"source\": \"memory\",\n      \"citation\": \"memory/2026-04-15.md#L26-L61\",\n      \"corpus\": \"memory\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"id\": \"edf4997b53453c30887e3a5982b7b9e47c97681ecf026e21185aba6e71cd7969\",\n      \"path\": \"memory/2026-04-14.md\",\n      \"startLine\": 1,\n      \"endLin